description:
TASKS & RESPONSIBILITIES
• Processing of Operations data for information and visualization
• Contact person for data analytics topics in Operations, in particular for the formulation of requirements for global BI solutions related to sales
• Close cooperation with Operations Controlling and Business Intelligence
• Harmonization/standardization of KPIs
• Initiation, management, and participation in projects relating to data analytics and predictive analytics
• Quality assurance of the available data
• Identify data driven potentials for process improvements
• You evaluate and translate complex functional and technical requirements (application and technical layers) into assignable deliverables and technical work packages in order to implement the desired solution.
• You contribute to new projects and evaluate their fit into the existing architecture and potentially extend the existing architecture of necessary
• You create use cases for Proof-of-Concepts and user stories for... behaviour-driven development
• You perform research for new technologies and best practices.
• Internal Stakeholders Management
QUALIFICATIONS
• Completed technical or commercial education
• Practical experience of 3 years minimum preferred
• Sound training in mathematics, statistics, computer science or similar.
• Experience in the field of data science and/or machine learning projects
• Enthusiasm for numbers, data, analysis and visualization
• Experience working with databases and creating reports in Power BI
• Knowledge of a programming language (eg: Python, R) beneficial
• High customer orientation in combination with enthusiasm for solving complex data-based tasks
• Well organized and structured person with hands on implementation skills
• Enjoys working in a creative, dynamic, and global team
• open and communicative, willingness to learn, self-reliant;
• fluent in spoken / written German or English
• Additional language skills are a plus
WE OFFER
• a challenge with room for implementing your own ideas and concepts;
• a creative job in one of the coolest environments in the industry;
• a tangible and heartfelt opportunity to learn and grow with us;
• cooperation in an interdisciplinary and diverse global team;
• good work-life balance thanks to flexible working hours and the freedom to organize your work;
• performance-related compensation and attractive incentive schemes;
• career planning, personal and management development programs;
• opportunity to gain international experience;
• voluntary fringe benefits provided by our company health management scheme PALfit;
OTHER
• willingness to travel up to 30%;
• location Bergheim;
• excellent business English and German;
• fulltime;

Minimum gross salary according to Austrian metal industry collective agreement is EUR 46.346,72 per year. We are willing to overpay according to training and qualification. We are looking forward to your informative application including salary expectations and a possible entry date

